title: Shark washes up on beach bitten IN HALF as fears grow of lurking sea monster

locations.name: volusia county beach safety ocean rescue

text:
VOLUSIA COUNTY BEACH SAFETY OCEAN RESCUE/GETTY/CORBIS HORROR: A sea monster is believed to be lurking off the Florida coast 
The stricken predator was originally five-feet long and the find has sparked fears there is a huge Great White Shark stalking the bay. 
Found on Saturday on New Smyrna Beach, Florida, many believe it was eaten by a legendary 14-foot monster shark named Katherine. 
A Volusia County Beach Safety Ocean Rescue lifeguard took a picture of the dead shark with pictures shared on social media showing it with the bottom half of its body missing. 
VOLUSIA COUNTY BEACH SAFETY OCEAN RESCUT ATTACKED: A shark was ripped in two – but what did it? Up close with sharks These fearless divers get VERY close to some deadly Tiger sharks in the Bahamas. 1 / 16 Caters News Agency Close encounter! as a group of brave divers came face-to-face with this deadly Great White 
Beach safety spokeswoman Tammy Morris said it was an adult blacktip which is itself responsible for 16% of shark attacks on humans around Florida. 
Tammy said the identity of the predator remains a mystery but suggested it could be the elusive Katherine. 
She added: “It is unknown what type of predator bit the shark or how far offshore it was when it was attacked.” 
The lifeguard posted the photo on social media with the caption: “Anyone up for a swim? LOL I guess there is something even bigger out there. #blacktip #whereiskatherine” Petting a GREAT WHITE shark? Are you insane?! Thursday, 16th February 2017 Photographer Jean Marie Ghislain had an astonishing encounter with the largest predator in the world: the Great White shark. He came across the beast while off the coast of Guadelupe. The sharks can grow to 20 feet in length and weigh up to 2,000 kilograms. 1 / 10 Caters News Agency At this point, you'd probably start regretting thinking it was a good idea to pet a Great White “I guess there is something even bigger out there” Tammy Morris 
Morris said that half-eaten sharks rarely wash ashore but she has seen it happen before. 
Katherine was last spotted in the seas around Florida last month. 
Back in Britain, fears emerged a Great White Shark was prowling the British coast . 
Mysterious half-eaten sea animals found on a beach in Great Yarmouth, Norfolk earlier this month, sparking concern among locals. 
While in a set of stunning images a diver revealed that not all Great White Sharks are aggressive . 
He was snapped patting the monster predator while it bares its teeth. Related articles
